parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt can cause the belt to become stuck or inoperable, potentially leading to accidents or injuries due to the lack of proper restraint.
symptoms: The seat belt is stuck in the up position
the seat belt does not retract
the seat belt feels like it is locking around the passenger or driver
the shoulder belt does not move
the cable pulled away from the guide rail
the motorized restraint is inoperative
the seat belt will not restrain the occupant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the guide rail can cause the seat belt cable to drop out of the chamber, leading to the shoulder belt anchorage becoming stuck and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The cable pulled away from the guide rail
the shoulder belt anchorage becomes stuck
the guide rail does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized restraint can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, potentially leading to accidents or injuries due to the lack of proper restraint.
symptoms: The motorized restraint is inoperative
the passenger side motorized restraint is inoperative
the driver side motorbelt is defective.
